        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 21 at 6:28PM MDT by NWS Rapid City SD</headline>
        <description>At 628 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 5
miles south of Nisland, or 13 miles east of Belle Fourche, moving
east at 30 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Newell, Nisland, Vale, Fruitdale, and southeastern Belle Fourche
Reservoir.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

A Severe Thunderstorm Watch remains in effect until 1100 PM MDT for
northwestern and west central South Dakota.</instruction>
